// multithreading
we know the process , inside the process that is called thread :
 now handling the thread and assigning the different task to any processor called multithreading

now what is time slicing
so the time slicing is nothing but the dividing the CPU time that divide CPU time is called
'QUANTA'
now the OS scheduler take this quanta and assign to the particular thread and process
and make sure that each thread gets the same time and preventing the particular thread or process to monopolizing the
time.


Context Switching
// context switching is nothing when a time slice is about to end os scheduler assign the new time slice to the next
waiting thread or process and then come back and resume the operation with previously held thread it is called context
switching.

